718002f-a.text:
(1)
Canal Street north side, west from and including Elizabeth Street.
August 30, 1927.

F.L. Sperr.

(2)
The same.  Nos. 167 to 183 Canal Street, the row of 5-story buildings in the immediate foreground, extending from Elizabeth to Mott Streets, were known as the St. Nicholas Buildings and were erected in 1856.
February 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

719636f-a.text:
28 to 2 Elizabeth Street, east side, south from Canal to Bayard Streets, showing the rears of the former Atlantic Gardens (pitched roof, No. 24-22) and the Thalia Theatre (adjacent). Today (1937) these have been replaced by a 1-story business structure. See the Bowery for further
views and data.
July 26, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
